Job Description:
Teach English to learners aged 10 to 18, in small class settings (from individual tutoring to groups of up to 24), for 90-minute lessons;
Follow our curriculum and manage assigned classes with care and consistency;
Understand the teaching content and apply effective, student-centered teaching methods;
Complete lesson planning and prepare all necessary materials in advance;
Monitor student progress closely and support them in improving areas of weakness;
Administer regular assessments and share student progress updates with parents and/or students as required;
Develop supplementary materials and test content based on assigned topics.

Job Requirements:
A Bachelor’s degree in English Language, English Education, or a related field. Candidates from other majors are warmly welcome if they have relevant teaching experience;
Experience in preparing students for high school entrance exams or the Vietnamese National Exam is a strong plus;
A passion for teaching and a genuine desire to grow in the field of education;
At least 1 year of experience teaching English grammar.

